# Build Observer Self-Maintenance

## Question

Standing call (Joel, 2026-07-14): "observer should occasionally systems
check itself, garden open panes, reflect on its state in the system for
observation." Add a periodic self-maintenance behavior to the observer
family (a tick step or its own cadence, e.g. every Nth tick):

- **Systems check**: family integrity (dispatcher alive on current
  release, tick log healthy, dedupe state sane, telemetry watch state
  fresh, unpublished observation backlog size).
- **Pane gardening**: close/adopt stray panes in the observer herdr
  session (dead workers, too-small retries, stale labels) — the
  2026-07-14 dispatcher too-small loop and w2/w3 sprawl are the case
  studies; supervisor-owned, deterministic, receipts logged.
- **Self-reflection for observation**: a periodic observation page about
  the observer's own state (pages written, spend, anomalies it raised,
  what it fixed) — the loop observing itself, same schema, same noise
  bar; feeds the masthead and the reflector like everything else.

Constraints: deterministic where possible, pi judgment only behind the
existing schemas; never touch panes outside the observer session; the
self-page respects the noise bar (no daily empty navel-gazing — write
only when there's signal).
